1
00:00:59,945 --> 00:01:03,585
It's okay. It's okay.

2
00:01:14,945 --> 00:01:17,625
<i>Whenever we talk</i>
<i>about investigative agencies,</i>

3
00:01:17,705 --> 00:01:21,945
<i>agencies like RAW, IB, CBI come to mind.</i>

4
00:01:22,025 --> 00:01:26,025
<i>Very few people are aware that Customs</i>
<i>also has an intelligence department.</i>

5
00:01:26,105 --> 00:01:30,465
{\an8}<i>Which is known as COIN,</i>
<i>Customs Overseas Intelligence Network.</i>

6
00:01:30,545 --> 00:01:35,545
<i>I'll explain the work</i>
<i>of COIN officers with a demo.</i>

7
00:01:40,825 --> 00:01:43,905
<i>This is one</i>
<i>of our IPL superstar cricketers.</i>

8
00:01:43,985 --> 00:01:45,745
<i>He is an all-rounder in everything.</i>

9
00:02:26,985 --> 00:02:29,505
<i>He was in Rome for vacation.</i>

10
00:02:30,065 --> 00:02:32,665
<i>He did some shopping,</i>
<i>along with sightseeing.</i>

11
00:03:06,265 --> 00:03:08,825
<i>By some shopping,</i>
<i>I mean it was worth 10-15 crores.</i>

12
00:03:35,345 --> 00:03:37,705
<i>The reality is, if you shop in Italy,</i>

13
00:03:37,785 --> 00:03:39,945
<i>you can claim a VAT refund at the airport</i>

14
00:03:40,025 --> 00:03:42,705
<i>on your way back to your home country.</i>

15
00:03:42,785 --> 00:03:45,625
<i>VAT is similar to the GST we have here.</i>

16
00:03:46,305 --> 00:03:48,465
<i>VAT is 22% here.</i>

17
00:03:48,545 --> 00:03:52,425
<i>And the one watch our cricketer</i>
<i>has purchased itself is worth 2 crores.</i>

18
00:03:52,505 --> 00:03:54,065
Yes, yes, sir.

19
00:03:55,025 --> 00:03:57,625
We certainly value the client…

20
00:03:57,705 --> 00:03:58,545
My pleasure.

21
00:04:12,065 --> 00:04:15,465
<i>Since our cricketer</i>
<i>did shopping worth 10-15 crores,</i>

22
00:04:15,545 --> 00:04:20,265
<i>his total VAT refund</i>
<i>comes to 2.5 to 3 crores rupees.</i>

23
00:04:20,345 --> 00:04:23,145
<i>Our cricketer really enjoys the fact</i>

24
00:04:23,225 --> 00:04:25,384
<i>that not only has he saved crores in duty,</i>

25
00:04:25,465 --> 00:04:29,385
<i>but he is also getting cashback</i>
<i>by taking a VAT refund in Italy.</i>

26
00:04:34,305 --> 00:04:36,225
<i>This is where COIN,</i>

27
00:04:36,305 --> 00:04:39,185
<i>that is Customs Intelligence Network,</i>
<i>enters the scenario.</i>

28
00:04:40,265 --> 00:04:43,545
<i>I won't share too many details</i>
<i>or you guys will also become alert.</i>

29
00:04:44,385 --> 00:04:47,465
<i>But you better know that COIN officers</i>

30
00:04:47,545 --> 00:04:50,105
<i>keep an eye</i>
<i>on every big transaction abroad.</i>

31
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:54,065
<i>And they share this information</i>
<i>with the Indian Customs immediately.</i>

32
00:05:02,785 --> 00:05:05,705
Hey, buddy! I've just landed.

33
00:05:06,345 --> 00:05:08,585
So where do you want to meet up?

34
00:05:29,305 --> 00:05:31,425
<i>And when our favorite cricketer</i>

35
00:05:31,505 --> 00:05:34,025
<i>crosses the green channel</i>
<i>without paying any duty,</i>

36
00:05:34,105 --> 00:05:36,745
<i>AIU is right there to welcome him.</i>

37
00:05:36,825 --> 00:05:38,345
<i>Courtesy COIN officer.</i>

38
00:05:38,425 --> 00:05:40,065
Just a sec. How many bags do you have?

39
00:05:40,145 --> 00:05:43,545
- Are these your check-in bags?
- Yes. Four bags.

40
00:05:43,625 --> 00:05:46,145
- You did a lot of shopping.
- What?

41
00:05:46,865 --> 00:05:49,225
- Do you have the papers for this?
- Excuse me.

42
00:05:51,625 --> 00:05:53,985
<i>It was with the help of my colleague,</i>
<i>COIN Officer Govind</i>

43
00:05:54,065 --> 00:05:56,825
<i>that I helped Priya escape from Al Dera.</i>

44
00:05:58,065 --> 00:06:00,265
Just a sec. Excuse me.

45
00:06:15,905 --> 00:06:17,425
Just a sec. Move please.

46
00:07:49,745 --> 00:07:52,625
Yes. Okay?

47
00:07:54,745 --> 00:07:55,865
Okay, Ramesh bhai.

48
00:07:56,545 --> 00:07:58,265
Customs has nabbed
them all with the stuff.

49
00:07:58,345 --> 00:08:00,665
- What are you saying?
- They even got Aslam and Mukim.

50
00:08:00,745 --> 00:08:01,585
Dammit!

51
00:08:03,025 --> 00:08:06,505
Rahul! Yes. Yes, okay.

52
00:08:07,505 --> 00:08:08,665
Start the car. Hurry.

53
00:08:15,145 --> 00:08:18,105
<i>Mumbai Customs nabbed 1,200 crore</i>
<i>of smuggled goods today in one shift.</i>

54
00:08:18,185 --> 00:08:19,785
WHOLE TRUTH
BEHIND THE SMUGGLERS' ARREST

55
00:08:19,865 --> 00:08:23,385
<i>They caught 500 kilos of gold,</i>
<i>2500 micro GPU chips,</i>

56
00:08:23,465 --> 00:08:26,985
<i>hundred kilos of cocaine</i>
<i>and many expensive watches.</i>

57
00:08:27,065 --> 00:08:30,345
<i>With this huge seizure,</i>
<i>Mumbai Customs has set a new record.</i>

58
00:08:30,425 --> 00:08:33,545
{\an8}<i>The operation led</i>
<i>by Assistant Commissioner Prakash Kumar</i>

59
00:08:33,625 --> 00:08:37,065
{\an8}<i>was a huge success</i>
<i>and a big blow to the smuggling syndicate.</i>

60
00:08:37,144 --> 00:08:39,784
{\an8}<i>It was a team effort</i>
<i>and entire credit goes to my team.</i>

61
00:08:39,865 --> 00:08:42,625
{\an8}<i>I also want to thank my seniors</i>
<i>for giving us full support.</i>

62
00:08:42,705 --> 00:08:44,904
{\an8}<i>It wouldn't have been possible</i>
<i>without them.</i>

63
00:08:44,985 --> 00:08:48,505
{\an8}<i>If so much gold was seized in one day,</i>

64
00:08:48,585 --> 00:08:52,345
{\an8}<i>just imagine how much gold</i>
<i>must be entering India illegally.</i>

65
00:09:00,225 --> 00:09:01,825
Salaam alaikum, Omar sahib.

66
00:09:02,465 --> 00:09:06,185
Yes, I was also watching that. I'll do it.

67
00:09:08,905 --> 00:09:11,985
Help him. Help him.

68
00:09:12,065 --> 00:09:13,785
Tie up!

69
00:09:14,305 --> 00:09:15,465
Tie Up. Slowly, slowly.

70
00:09:15,545 --> 00:09:17,545
Help him. Lift it up.

71
00:09:19,265 --> 00:09:20,865
Slowly, slowly. Close the door.

72
00:09:26,945 --> 00:09:27,825
Anna.

73
00:09:27,905 --> 00:09:30,585
<i>The chic conned us in collusion</i>
<i>with the Customs, Choudhary sahib.</i>

74
00:09:30,665 --> 00:09:33,425
Let's get a few of them killed,
they'll all come around.

75
00:09:34,145 --> 00:09:36,665
Killing government officers
like this is not right.

76
00:09:37,345 --> 00:09:39,545
It's only once in awhile
they do their duty.

77
00:09:40,385 --> 00:09:42,105
Try explaining it to them one more time.

78
00:09:42,185 --> 00:09:43,305
Okay, Choudhary sahib.

79
00:09:43,385 --> 00:09:45,265
I want that girl, Anna.

80
00:09:45,345 --> 00:09:48,465
<i>I've put my men on her trail,</i>
<i>Choudhary sahib. Don't you worry.</i>

81
00:10:09,425 --> 00:10:11,585
Excuse me! Sir, sir!

82
00:10:11,665 --> 00:10:13,945
- What are you doing?
- I'm cleaning the stains.

83
00:10:14,025 --> 00:10:17,385
- This is not allowed, sir.
- Hey, don't waste your time on me.

84
00:10:17,465 --> 00:10:20,465
There is a box of brass inside this,
which has my medicines.

85
00:10:20,545 --> 00:10:23,865
That stupid in-line officer of yours
thought it to be a gold brick.

86
00:10:23,945 --> 00:10:25,785
- Please come with me.
- Why?

87
00:10:25,865 --> 00:10:27,345
I want to check your bag.

88
00:10:27,425 --> 00:10:29,425
I won't let you do that. What'll you do?

89
00:10:29,505 --> 00:10:32,225
- What did you say?
- I won't let you.

90
00:10:32,305 --> 00:10:33,585
Sir, please come with me.

91
00:10:33,665 --> 00:10:35,425
Who gave authority to people like you?

92
00:10:35,505 --> 00:10:38,065
I'm not here to give you
the name of who did or didn't--

93
00:10:38,145 --> 00:10:40,145
Two guys went with contraband
behind your back.

94
00:10:40,225 --> 00:10:42,145
- And you are after me?
- Come with me, please.

95
00:10:42,225 --> 00:10:44,385
- I'm not going.
- It's you, Saxena sahib!

96
00:10:45,465 --> 00:10:48,065
- How are you, sir?
- How do you know me?

97
00:10:48,905 --> 00:10:50,745
Sir, I'm Superintendent Arjun Meena.

98
00:10:52,385 --> 00:10:54,305
I attended your lecture in Delhi.

99
00:10:55,105 --> 00:10:56,945
- Yes.
- Your lecture was awesome, sir.

100
00:10:57,705 --> 00:10:59,585
Explain it to this fool.

101
00:11:04,305 --> 00:11:07,025
Sir, who was this man
who spoke to you like that?

102
00:11:07,105 --> 00:11:10,505
Shrikant Saxena sahib was
the most honest officer in Mumbai Customs.

103
00:11:11,505 --> 00:11:14,345
He is. He is the most honest officer.

104
00:11:14,425 --> 00:11:17,225
- Sir, I was checking his bag--
- No problem. Go.

105
00:11:17,305 --> 00:11:19,305
- Shall I go and apologize?
- No need. Go.

106
00:11:23,665 --> 00:11:26,505
- Come in.
- Good morning, sir. You asked for me?

107
00:11:27,705 --> 00:11:29,465
Thank you. Thank you, sir.

108
00:11:30,225 --> 00:11:31,545
Call you later, sir.

109
00:11:32,945 --> 00:11:34,265
Okay. Bye, sir.

110
00:11:36,585 --> 00:11:39,705
Good morning, young man.
Well done. Just well done.

111
00:11:41,345 --> 00:11:43,785
Good, you didn't inform me about the raid.

112
00:11:44,465 --> 00:11:47,065
I would have gotten distracted
during the conference.

113
00:11:47,145 --> 00:11:48,865
Sir, full credit goes to the team.

114
00:11:48,945 --> 00:11:52,465
It was entirely their doing.
They informed me at the last minute.

115
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:56,705
- You were busy with the foreign delegates.
- Oh, no. You did the right thing.

116
00:11:56,785 --> 00:11:58,025
I'd have done the same.

117
00:11:58,105 --> 00:12:01,225
Okay, how's the investigation
coming through?

118
00:12:01,305 --> 00:12:03,865
Sir, the drug smugglers
have been taken into judicial custody.

119
00:12:03,945 --> 00:12:06,945
And gold smugglers
are being gently interrogated by my team.

120
00:12:11,705 --> 00:12:13,025
Very good.

121
00:12:13,825 --> 00:12:16,385
Now, go home fast and pack your bags.

122
00:12:16,465 --> 00:12:20,025
- You have to leave for Bangkok urgently.
- Bangkok, sir?

123
00:12:20,105 --> 00:12:23,225
Finance Secretary-level talks
are being held there.

124
00:12:23,745 --> 00:12:26,385
Gupta was supposed to go, but he is sick.

125
00:12:27,025 --> 00:12:28,745
You'll have to substitute for him.

126
00:12:28,825 --> 00:12:32,305
- Sir, there's a lot of workload here.
- There's nothing much.

127
00:12:32,945 --> 00:12:36,345
Don't worry. You have a great team. Right?

128
00:12:36,425 --> 00:12:39,465
They'll manage. You're flying out tonight.

129
00:12:40,145 --> 00:12:43,225
My PA will give you
the briefing note, okay?

130
00:12:45,785 --> 00:12:48,465
- Priya, ready?
- Yeah.

131
00:12:52,545 --> 00:12:55,305
CUSTOMS ACT
60 GLORIOUS YEARS

132
00:13:09,505 --> 00:13:10,345
Sir.

133
00:15:34,905 --> 00:15:37,065
Hey, stop! Stop, you bastard!

134
00:15:38,585 --> 00:15:40,065
Hello. All well?

135
00:15:40,145 --> 00:15:41,425
Yes, all is well.

136
00:15:41,505 --> 00:15:43,185
We've reached the safe house.

137
00:15:43,265 --> 00:15:44,545
Good.

138
00:15:46,425 --> 00:15:48,185
Is…

139
00:15:49,105 --> 00:15:50,705
Just a sec. I'll hand it over.

140
00:15:56,945 --> 00:15:59,945
Priya, it's Arjun.

141
00:16:04,985 --> 00:16:05,825
Hello!

142
00:16:05,905 --> 00:16:06,745
You okay?

143
00:16:08,065 --> 00:16:09,505
I'll see you tonight.

144
00:16:12,665 --> 00:16:14,265
- Bye.
- Bye.

145
00:16:17,825 --> 00:16:22,305
Mitali! Mitali! You'll kill him.
Come on, let's go.

146
00:16:24,345 --> 00:16:25,505
Easy. Calm down.

147
00:16:26,185 --> 00:16:27,185
Calm down.

148
00:16:29,825 --> 00:16:31,145
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

149
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:33,305
- Well done, guys.
- Thank you, sir.

150
00:16:35,665 --> 00:16:36,785
Man of the match!

151
00:16:38,785 --> 00:16:40,905
The hero of this raid.

152
00:16:40,985 --> 00:16:43,345
- Patel sahib!
- Congratulations, sir.

153
00:16:43,425 --> 00:16:45,585
- You killed it. Good.
- Hey, you crushed it.

154
00:16:45,665 --> 00:16:49,665
What killed it? I was trying to be a hero
and ended up losing 50 lakh rupees.

155
00:16:49,745 --> 00:16:52,705
Now I'll have to take a loan
to send my daughter to Canada.

156
00:16:52,785 --> 00:16:56,345
Ever heard of a Customs Superintendent
taking a loan, have you?

157
00:16:56,425 --> 00:16:58,865
That's how things work in this team,
Patel sahib.

158
00:16:58,945 --> 00:17:01,665
So, let's toast to celebrate his loss…

159
00:17:01,745 --> 00:17:03,265
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

160
00:17:03,345 --> 00:17:04,705
Bottoms up, sir.

161
00:17:04,785 --> 00:17:06,945
- Okay. Cheers. Sit.
- Please sit.

162
00:17:07,025 --> 00:17:07,945
Please sit, sir.

163
00:17:10,145 --> 00:17:14,505
Sir, I had a question. I've heard there's
a cap on our reward money. Is that true?

164
00:17:14,585 --> 00:17:19,105
Dhuria. Now you want a reward
just for doing your duty?

165
00:17:19,184 --> 00:17:22,145
- No, sir. I was just asking--
- Hey, nothing wrong in asking.

166
00:17:22,224 --> 00:17:25,944
Do you have any idea
how much today's informer is going to get?

167
00:17:26,025 --> 00:17:27,865
- How much?
- Crores of rupees.

168
00:17:27,944 --> 00:17:31,065
My boy, if you love money,
then in your next life,

169
00:17:31,145 --> 00:17:34,265
forget about being a customs officer,
better be an informer.

170
00:17:34,345 --> 00:17:36,665
- Sir… What…
- Yes, bhai.

171
00:17:36,745 --> 00:17:38,225
Arjun!

172
00:17:38,305 --> 00:17:40,185
Prakash sir didn't come?

173
00:17:40,265 --> 00:17:43,545
He had to leave for Bangkok urgently.
Gujjar, come here for a sec.

174
00:17:43,625 --> 00:17:45,425
- Have some manchurian.
- Okay.

175
00:17:45,505 --> 00:17:47,585
- Go on, have some, ma'am.
- We got it for you.

176
00:17:47,665 --> 00:17:49,265
Oh, that! Strain it and give me.

177
00:17:49,345 --> 00:17:53,745
I saw the report.
You seized three luxury watches. Congrats.

178
00:17:54,905 --> 00:17:58,545
So, you want to keep
your informant a secret, asshole?

179
00:18:00,865 --> 00:18:03,785
You've kept yours a secret too.

180
00:18:05,145 --> 00:18:06,945
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

181
00:18:07,465 --> 00:18:10,505
Okay, listen. Meet me
in the detention room tomorrow morning.

182
00:18:10,585 --> 00:18:12,345
It's our turn to bat.

183
00:18:13,465 --> 00:18:15,625
- Just call me.
- I think alcohol gives a good kick.

184
00:18:15,705 --> 00:18:18,185
Okay, guys. Enjoy yourselves.
I have some work to do.

185
00:18:18,265 --> 00:18:20,625
What work do you have
at this hour of the night?

186
00:18:22,465 --> 00:18:25,425
It's girl trouble, guys. Girl trouble.

187
00:18:25,505 --> 00:18:26,545
- Bye.
- Good night.

188
00:18:26,625 --> 00:18:27,905
Bye, sir.

189
00:18:46,585 --> 00:18:48,265
- Bhasin, all okay?
- All okay, sir.

190
00:19:22,905 --> 00:19:23,905
Were you scared?

191
00:19:26,505 --> 00:19:27,345
No.

192
00:19:28,785 --> 00:19:30,745
I knew you had my back.

193
00:20:42,665 --> 00:20:44,145
Vincent!

194
00:20:47,705 --> 00:20:49,785
Thapa, pass the water.

195
00:21:06,625 --> 00:21:10,145
Start talking. Or the thrashing continues.

196
00:21:10,785 --> 00:21:13,065
Look, sahib. We are the middlemen.

197
00:21:13,705 --> 00:21:16,985
We get the goods.
And deliver it to the concerned party.

198
00:21:17,065 --> 00:21:19,305
Apart from that, we know nothing.

199
00:21:22,385 --> 00:21:24,505
You can thrash us all you want.

200
00:21:25,265 --> 00:21:27,425
Sahib, I want my lawyer.

201
00:21:27,505 --> 00:21:30,265
No. Your lawyer
won't be here for two days.

202
00:21:31,745 --> 00:21:34,065
Till then, we'll continue
with our hospitality.

203
00:21:35,865 --> 00:21:36,945
Come on, get moving.

204
00:21:46,825 --> 00:21:49,985
Arjun, if our beatings
leave any marks on their bodies,

205
00:21:50,065 --> 00:21:51,625
it could be a problem in court.

206
00:21:52,465 --> 00:21:56,025
Don't worry about that.
I have their medical certificates ready.

207
00:21:57,065 --> 00:21:59,185
But we need to get them to talk.

208
00:22:02,785 --> 00:22:05,585
Thapa? Here.

209
00:22:06,265 --> 00:22:07,905
Record a video. Carry on, bhai.

210
00:22:15,385 --> 00:22:18,025
- What are you doing, sahib?
- Recording a video. What else?

211
00:22:18,105 --> 00:22:19,425
What's the video for?

212
00:22:19,505 --> 00:22:21,825
So that all your neighbors
can see you getting thrashed.

213
00:22:22,985 --> 00:22:25,785
This clip will be forwarded
to all your pals, your girlfriends,

214
00:22:25,865 --> 00:22:29,065
your bhabhis in JJ Junction.

215
00:22:29,145 --> 00:22:30,185
You guys will be famous.

216
00:22:31,025 --> 00:22:33,305
Hey, listen. Take off his shorts.

217
00:22:34,385 --> 00:22:36,225
No, sir. Hey, don't!

218
00:22:36,305 --> 00:22:39,225
Sahib, if you want to make a video,
make a good one at least.

219
00:22:39,305 --> 00:22:40,585
Get some proper lighting.

220
00:22:40,665 --> 00:22:42,505
So our faces look decent.

221
00:22:43,385 --> 00:22:44,705
Turn off the camera, sir.

222
00:22:44,785 --> 00:22:46,625
- I will tell you everything.
- Hey, Mukim!

223
00:22:46,705 --> 00:22:47,905
To hell with this, bhai.

224
00:22:48,705 --> 00:22:50,225
My reputation in JJ Junction

225
00:22:50,305 --> 00:22:52,785
won't be scarred
just to safeguard the Gujarati.

226
00:22:52,865 --> 00:22:53,985
Turn off the camera, sir.

227
00:22:54,985 --> 00:22:56,065
Thapa?

228
00:23:00,745 --> 00:23:03,745
Hey! Get me some water.

229
00:23:04,345 --> 00:23:06,705
Get some tea for me. Get my clothes.

230
00:23:10,145 --> 00:23:12,665
Ramesh managed all of Choudhary's goods

231
00:23:12,745 --> 00:23:15,425
that landed in Mumbai.

232
00:23:51,825 --> 00:23:53,545
Where does Ramesh bhai live?

233
00:23:53,625 --> 00:23:55,145
He lives somewhere in Madh island.

234
00:23:55,225 --> 00:23:58,385
I have his number saved in my cell.
Under the name Boss number two.

235
00:23:59,425 --> 00:24:02,265
- Who is Boss number one?
- My wife.

236
00:24:06,305 --> 00:24:07,545
Unlock it.

237
00:24:14,505 --> 00:24:15,705
- Vincent.
- Yes, sir.

238
00:24:18,185 --> 00:24:21,385
Check who is there at DRI?
Go and get this Ramesh bhai.

239
00:24:21,465 --> 00:24:22,785
Sure, sir.

240
00:24:44,425 --> 00:24:45,265
Jai Hind, sir.

241
00:24:45,345 --> 00:24:48,185
Jai Hind, Prakash. Reached safely?

242
00:24:48,265 --> 00:24:49,345
Yes, sir.

243
00:24:49,425 --> 00:24:51,545
- I was just leaving for the embassy.
<i>- Good.</i>

244
00:24:51,625 --> 00:24:54,385
<i>Somebody is waiting for you</i>
<i>outside your room. Go, meet him.</i>

245
00:24:54,945 --> 00:24:56,945
Who wants to meet me in Bangkok, sir?

246
00:24:57,025 --> 00:25:01,145
That's the surprise. Hurry up, go.

247
00:25:01,225 --> 00:25:02,065
Right, sir.

248
00:25:27,465 --> 00:25:29,025
Yes, Arjun? What's the status?

249
00:25:29,105 --> 00:25:31,305
Sir, we got Mukim's statement.

250
00:25:31,385 --> 00:25:35,065
The Ramesh bhai he is talking about
has direct links to Bada Choudhary.

251
00:25:35,145 --> 00:25:36,745
We are going to get Ramesh bhai.

252
00:25:36,825 --> 00:25:38,905
That's good news. Keep me updated.

253
00:25:43,465 --> 00:25:45,825
- How are you, Prakash <i>ji?</i>
- I'm good.

254
00:25:45,905 --> 00:25:47,065
Please come.

255
00:26:17,265 --> 00:26:19,185
Welcome to Bangkok, Prakash <i>ji.</i>

256
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:22,665
Ranjeet. Ranjeet Choudhary.

257
00:26:27,905 --> 00:26:31,625
My photos published in papers
have my name as Bada Choudhary.

258
00:26:42,425 --> 00:26:45,305
Hey, guys. I'm working on a play.

259
00:26:45,385 --> 00:26:48,105
So, there's a Madrasi character,
Bala Nair in the play.

260
00:26:49,025 --> 00:26:51,105
Will anybody help me prep for the role?

261
00:26:51,185 --> 00:26:53,025
Yes, I can help you.

262
00:26:53,105 --> 00:26:56,345
You have to learn the difference
between a Madrasi and a Malyali.

263
00:26:59,145 --> 00:27:01,265
Hey, look! There's Meenakshi with a baldy.

264
00:27:01,345 --> 00:27:02,385
Where?

265
00:27:05,385 --> 00:27:06,825
Was that guy bald?

266
00:27:08,705 --> 00:27:10,545
He's saying it was a baldy.

267
00:27:12,825 --> 00:27:15,785
- Why are you laughing?
- Sir, sorry. Sir, he--

268
00:27:15,865 --> 00:27:17,265
How long have you been in service?

269
00:27:17,345 --> 00:27:19,665
Sir, I… I'm sorry, sir.

270
00:27:19,745 --> 00:27:21,865
Rascal, you're on probation
and laughing at a senior?

271
00:27:21,945 --> 00:27:23,585
No, sir. No, sir.

272
00:27:23,665 --> 00:27:25,385
- Sorry, sir.
- How dare you?

273
00:27:25,465 --> 00:27:28,385
- Sir, sorry, sir.
- Do you wanna stay in the job or not?

274
00:27:28,465 --> 00:27:31,625
Yes, yes. Sorry, sir.

275
00:27:34,145 --> 00:27:36,025
This is what you call acting.

276
00:27:39,145 --> 00:27:43,225
- What's this school bag you carry around?
- This… is just like…

277
00:27:43,305 --> 00:27:44,785
- Hey.
- What are you doing?

278
00:27:51,665 --> 00:27:52,665
Bhai.

279
00:27:54,905 --> 00:27:55,745
Bhai.

280
00:27:57,745 --> 00:27:59,545
Bhai, why are you stressing?

281
00:28:00,305 --> 00:28:02,385
My words carry no value.

282
00:28:02,985 --> 00:28:05,345
I'll change my statement
before the magistrate.

283
00:28:14,865 --> 00:28:18,305
Here. Your wife's calling. Talk to her.

284
00:28:23,625 --> 00:28:26,745
Hello. <i>Salaam alaikum,</i> Rubina.

285
00:28:27,305 --> 00:28:30,145
Yes. All well?

286
00:28:34,945 --> 00:28:36,265
Don't worry.

287
00:28:36,945 --> 00:28:38,345
I'll get bail in two days.

288
00:28:39,745 --> 00:28:40,745
Yes.

289
00:28:41,585 --> 00:28:42,545
Yes.

290
00:28:44,465 --> 00:28:47,665
Take care. <i>Allah hafiz.</i>

291
00:28:56,945 --> 00:29:00,025
Bhai, is <i>bhabhi</i> upset?

292
00:29:02,665 --> 00:29:05,905
Bhai. Don't be mad, bhai.

293
00:29:07,985 --> 00:29:09,985
Bhai, I forgot to tell you.

294
00:29:11,305 --> 00:29:15,225
You know, Reshma from Temkar Street?
She's started working in the godown line.

295
00:29:16,065 --> 00:29:18,505
Tell me, bhai. Does it look good?

296
00:29:35,905 --> 00:29:40,185
Complete all the formalities and draft
a request to the Ministry of Finance.

297
00:29:40,265 --> 00:29:41,105
Okay, sir.

298
00:29:45,345 --> 00:29:46,185
Hello?

299
00:29:46,265 --> 00:29:47,785
Why did you do this to me?

300
00:29:50,825 --> 00:29:52,265
Just a sec.

301
00:29:56,625 --> 00:30:00,465
Look, Prakash. I just arranged
the meeting so that you could go there--

302
00:30:00,545 --> 00:30:02,985
Sir, I held you in high regard.

303
00:30:04,385 --> 00:30:08,345
Prakash, you're still young. You don't
understand the limitations of our job.

304
00:30:09,425 --> 00:30:10,585
What did Choudhary say?

305
00:30:12,345 --> 00:30:15,465
First of all, I apologize
for calling you to Bangkok like this.

306
00:30:16,425 --> 00:30:18,345
Yes. There was no conference.

307
00:30:19,225 --> 00:30:20,865
I wanted to meet you.

308
00:30:22,985 --> 00:30:24,465
Why did you want to meet me?

309
00:30:26,545 --> 00:30:28,785
I want to be friends with you, Prakash <i>ji.</i>

310
00:30:30,745 --> 00:30:34,105
Enmity is a tremendous waste
of time and effort.

311
00:30:35,985 --> 00:30:39,705
I believe in the saying that money
can buy everything in this world.

312
00:30:40,865 --> 00:30:43,745
Those who say, it can't,
don't know how to shop well.

313
00:30:44,585 --> 00:30:46,825
And I consider myself
very good at shopping.

314
00:30:48,985 --> 00:30:51,305
My syndicate takes care of your boss,

315
00:30:51,385 --> 00:30:55,185
a lot of the officers
and staff at your airport.

316
00:30:55,265 --> 00:30:56,705
We run so many households.

317
00:30:56,785 --> 00:31:01,305
Daughters' marriages, kids' education,
hospital bills of many are taken care of.

318
00:31:03,305 --> 00:31:05,105
It's a very well-oiled system.

319
00:31:05,865 --> 00:31:09,865
It's smooth. And at its peak performance.

320
00:31:12,025 --> 00:31:14,785
And then, an officer like you steps in.

321
00:31:15,305 --> 00:31:18,505
And he brings along
a few more honest officers,

322
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:20,545
who become a threat to our system.

323
00:31:26,585 --> 00:31:28,745
And I don't like threats, Prakash <i>ji.</i>

324
00:31:30,625 --> 00:31:32,465
That's why I want to be friends with you.

325
00:31:34,865 --> 00:31:37,385
The system takes care
of a lot of people, a lot of families.

326
00:31:39,505 --> 00:31:43,825
And even I don't know
how far I'd go to protect them.

327
00:31:47,905 --> 00:31:50,385
Do you know what country means, Choudhary?

328
00:31:51,945 --> 00:31:54,505
It is much bigger
and greater than your system.

329
00:31:57,385 --> 00:32:00,745
You need 10-20 corrupt officers
to run your system, right?

330
00:32:01,905 --> 00:32:05,025
But just one honest person
is enough to run my country.

331
00:32:07,465 --> 00:32:11,625
Prakash <i>ji,</i> if I wish I can get you posted
at some prestigious foreign embassy.

332
00:32:11,705 --> 00:32:13,745
You can earn dollars and live in luxury.

333
00:32:15,225 --> 00:32:17,065
Or I can send you to Nathu La,

334
00:32:17,145 --> 00:32:20,225
where you'd be dealing with cheap products
from China in the biting cold.

335
00:32:21,785 --> 00:32:23,625
But what's the need for that?

336
00:32:23,705 --> 00:32:26,225
We have nothing personal
against each other.

337
00:32:27,625 --> 00:32:30,065
Then why are you
after my bread and butter?

338
00:32:30,145 --> 00:32:33,225
Because your business
is destroying my country.

339
00:32:33,305 --> 00:32:36,345
Breaking news. Your country
is already a wreck, Prakash <i>ji.</i>

340
00:32:37,705 --> 00:32:39,025
You better watch the news.

341
00:32:43,105 --> 00:32:44,825
Write down any amount you want.

342
00:32:45,505 --> 00:32:47,625
You and your team will get it every month.

343
00:32:47,705 --> 00:32:49,745
And you will also get a regular tip.

344
00:32:50,625 --> 00:32:53,105
So that your team's reputation
stays intact.

345
00:33:05,985 --> 00:33:07,865
This is our last meeting, Prakash <i>ji.</i>

346
00:33:12,785 --> 00:33:14,985
No. We will meet once more, Choudhary.

347
00:33:26,585 --> 00:33:28,905
Sir, you sent me to meet
a criminal under false pretenses.

348
00:33:28,985 --> 00:33:31,465
He's telling me
that he is running our department.

349
00:33:31,545 --> 00:33:33,705
Nobody is running anything here, Prakash.

350
00:33:34,385 --> 00:33:36,745
We all do what we can, for our survival.

351
00:33:37,745 --> 00:33:39,665
I suggest you not get too excited.

352
00:33:52,585 --> 00:33:54,705
- Open the gate.
- Sahib is not at home.

353
00:33:55,585 --> 00:33:56,545
You…

354
00:33:59,225 --> 00:34:00,905
- Come on, move.
- Come on.

355
00:34:00,985 --> 00:34:02,585
- Open the gate.
- Move.

356
00:34:03,545 --> 00:34:04,465
Come on.

357
00:34:19,145 --> 00:34:20,744
Vincent.

358
00:34:28,705 --> 00:34:31,784
Wait! You can go.

359
00:34:31,865 --> 00:34:33,665
- What is it?
- We are here for Ramesh bhai.

360
00:34:33,744 --> 00:34:35,344
He has gone on a pilgrimage.

361
00:34:35,425 --> 00:34:37,784
He'll be back in a month.
You can come then.

362
00:34:37,865 --> 00:34:39,784
We want to search the place.

363
00:34:47,585 --> 00:34:48,905
- Boys.
- Yes, sir.

364
00:35:42,465 --> 00:35:46,705
Hey, young man! Take off your shoes.
This is our temple.

365
00:35:47,905 --> 00:35:48,905
Wait.

366
00:36:01,105 --> 00:36:03,385
There's nothing in here. Move on.

367
00:36:16,945 --> 00:36:18,625
Let's check outside.

368
00:37:15,305 --> 00:37:18,625
He killed my son! He killed my son!

369
00:37:26,065 --> 00:37:29,505
Sir, I didn't do anything.
Sir, I swear, I didn't do anything.

370
00:37:29,585 --> 00:37:33,145
Sir, he had the gun in his hand. The gun
went off by itself during the scuffle.

371
00:37:33,225 --> 00:37:37,585
Sir, believe me. Sir, I swear. I did not
do anything. I did not do anything.

372
00:37:37,665 --> 00:37:40,625
Sir, he shot himself.
Sir, please believe me, sir.

373
00:37:42,745 --> 00:37:44,905
I swear, I did not do anything…

374
00:38:00,065 --> 00:38:01,265
Mukim.

375
00:38:01,905 --> 00:38:02,985
Mukim.

376
00:38:03,985 --> 00:38:05,265
Mukim!

377
00:38:07,145 --> 00:38:08,305
Mukim!

378
00:38:10,785 --> 00:38:13,425
These bastards killed my Mukim, sir!

379
00:38:13,945 --> 00:38:16,345
They killed him! Mukim!

380
00:38:18,905 --> 00:38:22,265
He killed Mukim!
He is the one who killed him, sir!

381
00:38:22,345 --> 00:38:23,745
Mukim!

382
00:38:23,825 --> 00:38:25,825
They killed my Mukim, sahib.

383
00:38:27,265 --> 00:38:28,705
Mukim!

384
00:38:29,985 --> 00:38:31,265
Mukim!

385
00:38:33,625 --> 00:38:34,625
Mukim!

386
00:42:29,105 --> 00:42:34,105
Subtitle translation by: Monika Saraf
